The paper proposes a novel design for traffic signal control using reinforcement learning, which involves learning directly from feedback. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of advanced learning techniques to improve urban transportation efficiency, which could fall under robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of city data, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for data analysis.
